subject: CBN
title: Hum Anat Kin Stdnt
info: introduction to human anatomy. emphasizes musculoskeletal anatomy germane to athletic training, biomechanics, exercise physiology, motor learning/development.

subject: CBN
title: Gross Anat & Embryo
info:
the course is divided into three units:  extremities and back, torso, and head & neck. lecture time is used for one of the following:  (1) a pre laboratory presentation (dissection reviewed), (2) a review (at the end of a unit), (3) a clinical correlation or (4) a didactic embryology lecture.  the division amonst these for academic year 1997-98 was as follows:

unit     pre lab/review/clin.corr.     embry.
ext/back          19                      3
torso                12                      6
head & neck    16                      3

laboratory dissections were apportioned as follows:  extremities & back (13 three-hour sessions, 39 hours); torso (15 two hour sessions, 30 hours); head & neck (6 two hour sessions).

subject: CBN
title: Human Neuroscience
info: survey of current neuroscience, particulary that related to medicine. molecular/cellular neuroscience, neuronal electrical properties, sensory systems, motor systems, limbic system, autonomic nervous system. lecture, lab.
